  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aims of this study are to determine whether antibiotics administered routinely in women
      presenting with premature rupture of membranes later than the 37+0 weeks of gestation can
      alter the rate of maternal and neonatal infection and to compare these rates between prompt
      (&lt; 12 hour) and delayed (≥ 12 hour) induction in the group of patients not submitted to
      antibiotic prophylaxis.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
